## MOBILE & RESPONSIVE ISSUES

The admin panel has ZERO `@media` queries in `index.css`. Every layout is fixed-width.

### Critical Mobile Fixes Needed

1. **OrdersPage.tsx** — Order detail drawer is `420px` fixed width. On mobile it overflows. Fix: `width: min(420px, 100vw - 16px)` or full-width drawer on mobile.

2. **KDSPage.tsx** — Hardcoded `grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr)`. On mobile, columns are ~80px wide. Fix: responsive grid `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr))`.

3. **index.css** — Add global breakpoints:
```css
/* Tablet */
@media (max-width: 768px) { ... }
/* Mobile */
@media (max-width: 480px) { ... }
```

4. **MenuPage.tsx** — 2-column and 3-column form grids never collapse. Fix: `grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr))`.

5. **Button.tsx / SharedUI.tsx** — Touch targets are 32px (below WCAG 48px minimum). Fix: `min-height: 44px` on all interactive elements.

6. **Layout.tsx** — "More" drawer is 3-column grid, too cramped on small phones. Fix: 2-column on `<480px`.

7. **Layout.tsx** — Z-index conflicts: modal overlay (50) === mobile menu overlay (50). Fix: establish z-index scale: sidebar=30, overlay=40, modal=50, toast=60.

